The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning algorithms to solve combinatorial games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The games also involve game theory (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA) as they can be played by multiple agents. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE) in their approach.
